comments: Plumlee (DET) and Tucker (HOU) briefly engage and disengage off ball.
Gordon (HOU) is moving alongside Plumlee's (DET) path and maintains a legal guarding position in the post.
Tate (HOU) moves forward into Grant's (DET) space and makes lower body contact during his jump shot attempt.
Tucker (HOU) is already in Wright's (DET) path when contact occurs and he does not deliver contact.
Plumlee (DET) makes marginal body contact with Oladipo (HOU) contesting his driving shot attempt.
Tucker (HOU) and Griffin (DET) make incidental contact with one another during rebounding.
Oladipo (HOU) swipes forward and makes contact with Griffin's (DET) head/face.
Plumlee (DET) is already in Tate's (HOU) path when contact occurs and he does not deliver contact.
Tate (HOU) wraps Plumlee (DET) off ball.
Tucker (HOU) is already in Ellington's (DET) path when contact occurs and he does not deliver contact.
Tucker (HOU) is already in Ellington's (DET) path and releases away from the contact.
Grant (DET) is jumping slightly forward towards Gordon (HOU) when Gordon extends his leg to initiate the marginal contact.
Plumlee (DET) moves alongside of Gordon (HOU) and makes marginal contact with him during his driving shot attempt.
Ellington (DET) is already in Tate's (HOU) path when contact occurs and he does not deliver contact.
Gordon (HOU) maintains legal guarding position as he defends Griffin (DET) in the post.
Gordon (HOU) legally contests Griffin's (DET) shot near the rim.
Griffin (DET) holds Gordon's (HOU) arm and restricts his ability to secure the rebound.
Brown (HOU) jumps into Griffin's (DET) body and makes contact with Griffin's arm that affects his shot near the rim.
Gordon (HOU) draws Plumlee (DET) into the air towards him and the contact results in a foul on Plumlee even if contact is initiated by Gordon.
Tate (HOU) extends his arm slightly forward when marginal contact with Griffin (DET) occurs.
Grant (DET) cleanly blocks Gordon's (HOU) shot attempt.
Grant (DET) legally contests Oladipo's (HOU) jump shot attempt.

Tucker (HOU) extends his arm slightly forward when some contact occurs to the head/neck area of Griffin (DET).   Contact to an opponent?s head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Tucker (HOU) extends his arms slightly forward when marginal contact with Grant (DET) occurs.
After communicating with the Replay Center, it was determined the foul occurred after the game clock expired and the game was over.
